<font color="#FF0000">VERIFICATION </font><br>
<tt>Sun Oct 26  7:43:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I would like to clear the air about recent accusations about Cook Barela being a wannabe Vietnam Vet.<br><br>
Not long after Cook began posting here, I asked a guy who served in the same unit as Cook, at roughly the same time(67-68), if he knew that there was another Marine on line who had served at Liberty Bridge.<br><br>
The other Marine actually lives in Washington County, Tennessee - which is next door to Greene County - where I reside. He has a nice website with pictures and makes mention of Liberty Bridge. Any who wish to visit his site may contact me b/c.<br><br>
The guy told me that he had talked to Cook the previous weekend, and yes, &quot;he (Cook) was at the bridge&quot;. That shows you how small the world has become because of the Internet. So as far as I am concerned, Cook was there.<br><br>
There are times when some of the dialogue on the Internet turns more technical than I am capable of understanding. It floats over my head. So it is harder for me to figure whether someone is  stretching the truth (lying). I don't know much about aircraft or ships or Special Ops, for instance. In that respect I could be easily fooled.<br><br>
The best way for me to figure if someone is telling a lie, is for them to give 2 different versions of the same story.<br><br>
Thanks Cook, for pointing out the lie that spatz told.<br><br>
There is no excuse for lying and claiming &quot;credit&quot; for lying down in front of a train. There is no excuse for posting inflammatory, abusive garbage on this site, then signing a fictitious name. The people who come here to contribute or to read, deserve better than that. <br><br>
We don't participate in order to &quot;win&quot;, we post in order to make known our own point of view. At least that is how I feel.<br><br>
Those who would stoop to lies and forgeries should be gone. You are ruining this site. You don't belong here. 
<p><code>-- wingman$greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


